<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Type locality. Gua Bama, Pahang (
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="4.193611">4°11'37&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="101.967224">101°58'2&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
) (Figure 18B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Distribution range. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Diplommatinidae" genus="Plectostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectostoma salpidomon" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salpidomon">Plectostoma salpidomon</taxonomicName>
can be found in many limestone hills in the valley in between the Titiwangsa, Tahan and Benom mountain ranges (Figure 18B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<pageBreakToken pageId="60" pageNumber="61" start="start">Conservation</pageBreakToken>
status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Least concern. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Diplommatinidae" genus="Plectostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectostoma salpidomon" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salpidomon">Plectostoma salpidomon</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution range. Living populations have been recorded in many limestone hills and some of these are in protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
